commitResults.messageTitle: Added A-TextUiTesting, moved tasks into another package
Add date parser for Deadline and Event class
commitResults.messageBody:
Date is treated as a normal string

Pib should be able to parse date and time so that it is able to
format it nicely for the list view

Let's encapsulate the function of parsing the date and time in the
Deadline and Event classes and add a public factory method to
process the raw string

commitResults.messageTitle: Add read and write to file functionality
commitResults.messageBody:
Pib resets the list everytime it is started

User has better experience if data can be saved and read
automatically

Let's add functionality to read from saved data and write any
changes to file

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code into more classes for more OOP
commitResults.messageBody:
Pib is having all the functionality in one class.

Having the functionalities split into classes follow OOP principles
better

Let's move Ui, Storage, TaskList and Parser into their own classes

Classes are all in the default package

Grouping classes in packages helps to standardize where similar
classes should be located

Let's create packages for some of these classes

Methods are not being unit tested

Unit testing some public methods help to ensure that changes made
will not cause these methods to lose their functionality

Let's add JUnit tests for Deadline and Todo classes

Methods would just call the print method instead of throwing
exceptions

Making methods throw exceptions and catching them at one place makes
it neater and more organized and predictable

Let's make methods throw exceptions instead of printing error messages

There is no find functionality

There will be better UX if user can search for tasks containing a
certain word

Let's add a find functionality to search for tasks

commitResults.messageTitle: Add and modified Javadocs for almost all public methods
commitResults.messageBody:
Public methods do not have proper documentation/javadocs after adding
and refactoring since last commit

Let's add proper javadocs for these public methods

commitResults.messageTitle: Modified storage to create new text file if it does not exist already
Add Gradle to support build and test automation
Add GUI for Pib using JavaFX
Add enableAssertions and modify mainClassName in build.gradle

commitResults.messageBody:
No assertions are in the code.

Having assertions helps to minimise programming errors on dev's side
when we change something elsewhere in the future.

Let's add assertions to places where objects could be null and where
string could be null or blank.

Code readability can be improved by modifying code structure

Better code quality helps to maintain the code in the future

Let's,
* implement SLAP
* refactor long methods and happy paths
